behavior.\",\n2418:       \"status\": \"implemented\",\n2419:       \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-06-profile-capabilities-verification\",\n2420:       \"sourceBehavior\": \"`Profile.kt` renders a back command, static profile action cards, and a logout button. The back arrow calls `navController.navigateUp()`, the action cards keep placeholder click handlers, and logout clears the start destination stack before routing to onboarding.\",\n2421:       \"targetBehavior\": \"`profile_route_service.cj` now centralizes the profile-specific back-route decision and logout transition state, while `renderProfileRoute` preserves the visible back affordance, static action cards, and logout button. `bootstrap_page.cj` delegates the profile logout flow through focused profile route-service and store endpoints before routing to onboarding after session logout, while edit and section taps remain inert like the source screen's empty click handlers.\",\n2422:       \"verificationEvidence\": [\n2423:         \"Manual source review confirmed `Profile.kt` owns the back icon, inert edit/action-card click surfaces, and logout navigation callback.\",\n2424:         \"Manual target review confirmed `profile_route_service.cj::resolveBackRoute`, `::canNavigateBack`, and `::buildLogoutTransition` now carry the profile-specific route decisions instead of closing the row through only the broad bootstrap shell.\",\n2425:         \"`profile_page.cj::buildProfileTopBar`, `::buildProfileSection`, and `::renderProfileRoute` preserve the visible back/logout/action-card surface while `profile_store.cj::logoutRoute` keeps the logout destination explicit.\",\n2426:         \"Final-coverage test build report PASS: `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/final-coverage/test-build-report.md` ran `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` from `entry/src/test/cangjie` successfully.\",\n2427:         \"Phase-06 build gate PASS: `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-06-profile-capabilities-verification/build-report.m